1.description: MiniZip in zlib through 1.3 has an integer overflow and resultant heap-based buffer overflow in zipOpenNewFileInZip4_64 via a long filename, comment, or extra field.
1.overview: This CVE was created for MiniZip (part of zlib/contrib/minizip), which is not used by Node.js. Node.js uses zlib for compression but does not use the MiniZip component where this vulnerability exists.

2.description: Inappropriate implementation in V8 in Google Chrome prior to 127.0.6533.99 allowed a remote attacker to potentially exploit heap corruption via a crafted HTML page.
2.overview: This V8 vulnerability does not fall within Node.js's threat model. The vulnerable code path is not exposed through Node.js APIs and cannot be exploited in normal Node.js usage.

3.description: Out of bounds write in V8. Type Confusion in V8. Type confusion in V8 in Google Chrome.
3.overview: These V8 vulnerabilities do not fall within Node.js's threat model. The vulnerable code paths are not exposed through Node.js APIs.

4.overview: These V8 vulnerabilities do not affect Node.js. The vulnerable functionality is not exposed in Node.js's implementation.

5.overview: This OpenSSL vulnerability does not affect Node.js. Node.js's usage of OpenSSL does not trigger the vulnerable code path.

6.overview: These OpenSSL vulnerabilities do not affect Node.js. Node.js's usage of OpenSSL does not trigger the vulnerable code paths.
